{{SupportPage|vendor=D-Link|model=DSM-750|vs_id=547}} "Digital Media Adaptor Main Board" and "REV-A1" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :"Digital Media Adapter USB Board", "REV-A1", and "8SM750U..2A1G" is silkscreened on the USB board. ==Probable used PSU(s)== This device has an internal power supply - the one shown in the FCC photos is a UOP325D-0512(S) ('''UNIFIVE''' manuf'ed?). It's a dual-output power supply (5V, 12V). There isn't a modular power connector on the case itself - it's corded. {{hasPowerSupply |brand=UNIFIVE |model=UOP325D-0512(S) |input_v=120 |input_a= |input_c=AC |input_hz= |input_conn=unknown |output_v= |output_a= |output_c=DC |output_conn=unknown |style=modular, internal |manuf_country= }}
